      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The docs system has one on-disk content format: "
        },
        {
          "insert": "doc.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", a normalized block tree, plus a "
        },
        {
          "insert": "comments.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " sidecar per bundle. Agents read through a pure markdown render and write through the same seven-op kernel the editor uses. That keeps reading greppable, writing enumerable, and file bytes deterministic enough for reviewable diffs."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-overview-scope-3": {
      "id": "b-00-overview-scope-3",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "This section is system-agnostic: it describes shapes and invariants, not transport wiring. Everything here is defined in pure TypeScript in "
        },
        {
          "insert": "packages/docs-model",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/docs-model"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — no React, no filesystem, no HTTP — so the browser, the Bun server, and the CLI share one definition. The model decomposes into five shapes, and each gets its own page."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
